PROJECT INTRODUCTION

The Online Food Ordering System is a web-based application designed to streamline and enhance the process of ordering food from various restaurants through the internet. This system aims to provide a convenient and efficient platform for users to browse menus, place orders, and make online payments, thereby eliminating the need for traditional phone-based ordering. Customers browse a digital menu, either on an app or website and place and pay for their order online. The Online Food Ordering System's main purpose is to maintain track of information such as item Category, Food, Delivery Address, Order, and Shopping Cart. It keeps track of information about item category, the Customer, the Shopping Cart, and the item Category. The system also incorporates real-time order tracking, allowing customers to monitor the status of their orders from preparation to delivery.

In conclusion, The Online Food Ordering System provides a comprehensive solution to meet the evolving demands of the food industry by offering a convenient, efficient, and secure platform for customers to order food and for restaurants to manage their operations effectively in the digital era. The system leverages modern technology to provide a user-friendly and efficient platform that caters to the growing demand for online food services.

 
SCOPE & PURPOSE

We propose to build a project that can efficiently handle and encompassing various aspects of the food industry and technology. A user-friendly platform or mobile application for customers to browse restaurants, view menus, place orders, customize preferences, and make payments. The business of restaurants and food is now growing constantly over the internet.

The future scope includes the expansion of technologies like java and
SQL we can also add new technologies and many more for improving the efficiency of the software.

